# umaassist Project Guidelines

## Code Style
- No comments in code unless complex logic requires explanation
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow existing naming conventions
- No emojis in code

## Project Structure
- Components in src/components/
- Pages in src/app/
- Utilities in src/lib/
- Types in src/types/

## Guides System
- All Champions Meeting guides go in src/components/Guides/guidesData.ts
- Use slug format: "cm-month-year" (e.g., "cm-december-2024")
- Always set isCurrent: true on new guide, false on old
- Team Trials is static - only update src/app/team-trials/page.tsx every 6 months
- Champions Meeting guides have dynamic routes at /guides/[slug]/page.tsx
- Use getCurrentCMGuide(), getCMGuideBySlug(), getAllCMGuides() from src/lib/guides.ts

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15
- React 19
- Tailwind CSS v4
- TypeScript
- next-themes for dark mode

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (MyComponent.tsx)
- Files: lowercase with hyphens (my-file.ts)
- Functions: camelCase (myFunction)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Database/Data
- Use guidesData.ts as single source of truth for CM guides
- Functions in lib/guides.ts query this data

## Do's and Don'ts
- DO: Use server components by default
- DO: Use the lib/guides.ts helper functions for guides
- DO: Add 'use client' only when needed (state, hooks, event listeners)
- DON'T: Add comments unless necessary
- DON'T: Use localStorage (not supported)
- DON'T: Create inline CSS, use Tailwind utilities only
- DON'T: Add emojis to code files